It’s understood the two were burnt beyond recognition in the accident that involved trucks and light motor vehicles. JOHANNESBURG - Two people have died on the N3 following an accident between Vosloorus and Heidelburg during a pile-up. It’s understood the two were burnt beyond recognition in the accident that involved trucks and light motor vehicles on Tuesday afternoon. Ekurhuleni EMS spokesperson William Ntladi said, “We have two people from one vehicle that were burnt beyond recognition as the vehicle caught fire in the pile-up. Two of the trucks are still burning.” 